The Toyota Avanza is a car produced in Indonesia by the Daihatsu manufacturer, which is also marketed by Daihatsu under the name Daihatsu Xenia. The first generation of this car was launched in December 2003.[1] The name \"Avanza\" comes from the Italian and Spanish avanzato/avanza, which means upgrade

\"The Honda HR-V is a mini SUV produced by Honda from 1998 to 2006 and then from 2014 to the present. The first generation HR-V was based on the Logo and was sold in Japan and several countries in Asia-Pacific from 1998 to 2006. .\"

\"The Brio is a 5-door subcompact hatchback car produced by Honda in Indonesia and Thailand. This car was introduced in March 2011.\"

\"The BMW X1 is a compact SUV in the luxury category produced by BMW and BMW Brilliance. The X1 is available with rear-wheel drive (sDrive) or all-wheel-drive (xDrive). The concept car was first introduced at the 2008 Paris Motor Show.\"

\"The BMW X2 (model code F39) is a subcompact luxury crossover SUV produced by BMW. It was first showcased as the BMW Concept X2 at the 2016 Paris Motor Show,[3] with a production version unveiled in October 2017.\"
